Description: Rim sherd of Chian Wild Goat Style pottery dinos; white slip; interior reserved; narrow black band on edges of rim; on top of rim (worn), double guilloche pattern;glaze at top of shoulder; inscription on exterior.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Aphrodite (Naukratis), Context Φ3?
Curator's comments: The number 'A788' is pencilled on the interior surface of the sherd. There is a label glued to the interior surface of the sherd upon which 'list 49' is written. Also 'T' and 'Φ3'. For parallels, see Boston 86.530.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GD.0003) (phase 2)
